videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young makes the great one-handed pass to find Brady Manek in stride for the easy dunk.
videos.headline: Young's vision leads to dunk

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young shows off his great ball handling skills and gets to the rim with ease.
videos.headline: Young's handles get him two

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young runs the inbounds play to perfection to find Christian James for three.
videos.headline: Young puts the ball on a string

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young floats up the perfect dime to Jamuni McNeace, who slams it down with two hands.
videos.headline: Young lobs it for McNeace

videos.description: Texas Tech's aggressive rebounding helps the Red Raiders' Niem Stevenson nail the 3-pointer and help energize the offense against Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Stevenson hits the field goal

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young continues to facilitate as he finds Brady Manek in the paint for the layup.
videos.headline: Young shows off impressive arm

videos.description: Trae Young makes only one field goal but goes 9-for-9 from the free throw line and dishes the ball well as Oklahoma leads Texas Tech 37-36 at the half.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Highlight (Young struggles in 1st half against Texas Tech) 02/13/2018 ESHEET SOT FULL

videos.headline: Young struggles in first half against Texas Tech

videos.description: Texas Tech's Keenan Evans finds Norense Odiase for the easy basket as Texas Tech extends their lead against Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Odiase slams it home

videos.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young gets lazy with his passing, as Texas Tech's Zhaire Smith steals it and the Red Raiders' unselfish offense leads to points.
videos.headline: Young's sloppy pass leads to Texas Tech basket

videos.description: Texas Tech's Niem Stevenson puts up the shot from the corner, as the Red Raiders pad their lead against Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Stevenson hits off-balance three

videos.description: Texas Tech's Keenan Evans blows by the defense, and finishes at the rim with a dunk.
videos.headline: Evans hops his way to the basket

videos.description: Texas Tech's Keenan Evans speaks on the Red Raiders' big home victory over Oklahoma and how they hope to use the momentum to carry them to a Big 12 championship.
videos.headline: Evans talks potential Big 12 run

videos.description: Trae Young is ice cold from the field, shooting 4-of-16 and scoring 19 points, as the No. 7 Red Raiders defeat the No. 23 Sooners 88-78.
videos.headline: Oklahoma falls to Texas Tech, suffers fourth consecutive loss
